## TypeScript Standards

**Imports & Exports:**
- Named exports only, declared inline: `export function myFunc()`
- NO default exports
- NO unnecessary `index.ts` files

**Functions & Components:**
- Use `function` keyword for named functions (not `const`)
- React component props: interface named `Props` (unless conflict/export needed)
- Use `interface` not `type` for props

**Code Quality:**
- Small files, small functions, clean code focus
- Comments mark bad code - refactor instead
- NO null types (use undefined)

**Tooling & Libraries:**
- Yarn for package management
- MUI for UI elements
- Zod for type guards
- Zustand for state management
- Axios-based API clients extending BaseApiClient

## Frontend Structure

```
src/
  stores/         # Zustand stores
  api/            # Backend interactions (Axios clients)
  components/     # Atomic reusable components
    SomeComponent/
      SomeComponent.tsx    # Main component
      SubComponent.tsx     # Subcomponents in same folder
  views/          # Non-reusable views with co-located components
  utils/          # Shared utilities
```

## General Principles

**Day 0 POC Philosophy:**
- NO fallbacks for errors - surface problems immediately
- NO premature optimization
- NO feature creep - stick to scope
- DO solve problems correctly - understand root causes
- Validate assumptions early with real data
